&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Mendaera, Inc.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mendaera is developing technology that will enable all healthcare providers to do more for their patients. Our platform combines real-time imaging, robotics, and artificial intelligence to make precise and consistent intervention more accessible. Our aim is to eliminate barriers in the patient journey, accelerate recovery, delight customers, and reduce cost of care.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Senior Electrical Engineer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Opportunity: &lt;/strong&gt;Mendaera is looking for a Senior Electrical Engineer to design, develop, implement and maintain hardware that automates surgical interventions based on real-time multimodal imaging and sensor information.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience with engaging Contract Manufacturers including: knowledge in the construction and build processes of PCBAs; experience with test procedure development; improving production yields. Support Manufacturing and In-Field operations by troubleshooting component and system level failures as they occur. Supporting, designing, and developing mixed-signal circuits used in motor driver applications, ADCs, and feedback sensor technologies. Generate analog and digital electrical designs supporting 32-bit microcontroller systems. Understanding and managing issues of signal and power integrity through first principles, circuit simulations, circuit modeling, and use case analysis. Knowledge of printed circuit board types including rigid, flex, rigid-flex, and HDI technologies. Lab testing of mixed-signal circuits and experience with using oscilloscopes, signal analyzers, signal generators, etc. to validate designs. Knowledge of ESD requirements, testing, and good practices. Working with product and safety systems teams to run DFMEA to ensure robust and safe products. Can work remotely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Must have a Master’s degree or foreign equivalent in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, or any other related degree.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Skills Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required skills must include any experience with each of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience with schematic capture and layout for printed circuit boards using CAD software (such as KiCAD, Eagle, Cadence, or Altium);&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience with prototyping new circuit functionality for small electronics devices;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience understanding and applying fundamental electrical engineering knowledge into practical applications of new technology development;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience working with Universal Serial Bus (USB) technology inclusive of USB2.0, USB3.0, USB Power Delivery, and USB Type-C connectors to implement a high-speed and high-power user-facing interface&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience design with high-speed signaling on printed circuit boards (such as DDR, HDMI, or USB3.0)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience interacting with contract manufacturers (CMs) to produce prototypes of new printed circuit board technology. #LI-DNI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Mendaera, Inc.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mendaera is developing technology that will enable all healthcare providers to do more for their patients. Our platform combines real-time imaging, robotics, and artificial intelligence to make precise and consistent intervention more accessible. Our aim is to eliminate barriers in the patient journey, accelerate recovery, delight customers, and reduce cost of care.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An Era of Empowered Intervention&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Mendaera, we aim to build collaborative AI and robotics in healthcare to ensure that the right procedures can be performed by the right providers, in the right places, for the right patients. We believe access to care can be radically expanded via technology. We are a team of contrarians, building a first-of-its-kind healthcare technology platform, designed to bring world-class interventional capability to the front lines of care. By fusing robotics, real-time imaging, and AI, we aim to remove friction from the patient journey that all-too-often leads to inconsistent, imprecise, or outright unavailable care. We intend to change the way minimally invasive healthcare is delivered.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a bold ambition. If it resonates with you, continue below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Product Manager Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Product Manager, you are expected to help drive the strategic direction for our pipeline offerings, and usher high-impact solutions from inception to commercial reality. This is a role for a technically-adept individual who thrives on solving the &quot;impossible&quot; through structured product thinking. You will spend your days at the intersection of the procedure room and the engineering lab. Your mission will be to help ensure our platform is capable, delightful, and accessible, in service of creating lasting value for every stakeholder in our ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a builder who views ambiguity as a blank canvas rather than a roadblock.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive in the high-velocity world of a startup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have an ability to &quot;zoom out&quot; to design high-level strategic frameworks and &quot;zoom in&quot; to ensure every detail is flawless.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a systems thinker by nature, and can build world-class work products from the ground up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a proactive problem-solver who obsesses over the &quot;why&quot; as much as the &quot;how”.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Immerse yourself in the clinical context in which we operate, via conducting market analysis, customer and stakeholder interviews, ethnographic studies, and user testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop deep clinical understanding of the clinical environments and procedures in which our platform is being used today – and will be used tomorrow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become an expert on the product, allowing you to help define and refine the product roadmap, including effective upstream needs-finding, value proposition refinement, and feature set prioritization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with commercial and engineering teams to translate user and business requirements into technical specifications, and managing trade offs during development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and track success metrics across entire product development lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
